# Agastya Healthcare — Cursor AI Rules
# Stack: Vue 3 + Spring Boot + FastAPI | DB: PostgreSQL (Supabase) | Healthcare Domain

---

## 🧠 Project Context

You are working on **Agastya Healthcare** — a telemedicine platform for patients and doctors.
- Frontend: Vue 3 (Composition API, Pinia, Vue Router, Axios)
- Backend: Spring Boot 3.x (Java 17+, JPA/Hibernate, Spring Security, JWT)
- AI/Chat Service: FastAPI (Python 3.11+)
- Database: PostgreSQL (Supabase) — migrating FROM MongoDB
- Video: Agora RTC SDK
- Payments: Razorpay
- Notifications: Email + MSG91 (SMS) + Firebase FCM

This is a **health/medical application**. All code must treat patient data as sensitive PII.
Never suggest storing plaintext health data, credentials, or tokens insecurely.

---

## 🗂️ Architecture Rules

### General
- Always separate concerns: controllers → services → repositories. Never put business logic in controllers.
- Never expose internal IDs (DB auto-increment) in API responses — always use `external_id` (UUID).
- All timestamps must be in UTC. Store as `TIMESTAMPTZ` in PostgreSQL.
- All deletions must be **soft deletes** — set `deleted = true`, never `DELETE FROM`.
- Every entity that stores patient data must have: `created_at`, `updated_at`, `deleted` fields.

### API Design
- REST endpoints follow: `/api/v1/{resource}/{id}/action`
- Use `external_id` (UUID) in all URLs, never DB primary key.
- All list endpoints must support pagination: `?page=0&size=20&sort=createdAt,desc`
- All API responses follow this envelope:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {},
  "message": "string",
  "timestamp": "ISO8601"
}
```
- Error responses must include an `errorCode` field (machine-readable), not just HTTP status.

---

## 🌿 Vue 3 Rules

### Auth & Security
- **NEVER store JWT tokens in `localStorage` or `sessionStorage`** — use `httpOnly` cookies only.
- Access tokens live in memory (Pinia store). Refresh tokens in `httpOnly` cookie only.
- All routes requiring auth must have `meta: { requiresAuth: true, role: 'PATIENT' | 'DOCTOR' | 'ADMIN' }`.
- Router guards must check both `isAuthenticated` AND `role` — redirect to `/unauthorized` on role mismatch, not `/login`.
- `SameSite=None; Secure=true` on refresh token cookie when frontend and API are on different origins.
- Scope refresh token cookie path to `/api/v1/auth/refresh` only.

### Composition API Patterns
- Always use `<script setup>` syntax — never Options API.
- Use `defineProps` with TypeScript types, never untyped props.
- Composables go in `src/composables/use{Name}.ts` — one concern per composable.
- Never call APIs directly in components — always through a composable or Pinia action.
- All API calls must handle loading, error, and success states explicitly.

```typescript
// ✅ Correct pattern
const { data, isLoading, error } = useAppointments()

// ❌ Never do this in a component
const res = await axios.get('/api/appointments')
```

### Agora Video Call Rules
- Agora token must ALWAYS come from Spring Boot backend — never generate client-side.
- Channel name must always equal `appointmentId` (UUID) — never use doctor/patient IDs.
- Always implement `token-privilege-will-expire` handler to renew token mid-call.
- Always clean up tracks on `onUnmounted`:
```typescript
onUnmounted(async () => {
  await localAudioTrack?.close()
  await localVideoTrack?.close()
  await client.leave()
})
```
- Always show network quality indicator using `client.on('network-quality', ...)`.
- Implement fallback to audio-only when video quality degrades below threshold 4.

### Component Rules
- Components in `src/components/{domain}/{ComponentName}.vue`
- Pages in `src/pages/{role}/{PageName}.vue` (role = patient | doctor | admin)
- Never use inline styles — use Tailwind utility classes only.
- All forms must have client-side validation before API call.
- All user-facing error messages must be human-readable (never expose raw API error).

---

## ☕ Spring Boot Rules

### Security
- Every controller endpoint must have `@PreAuthorize` annotation — never rely on route-level security alone.
- JWT filter must validate: signature, expiry, token type (access vs refresh).
- Implement refresh token rotation — invalidate old refresh token on each use.
- Rate limit all auth endpoints using Bucket4j:
  - `/auth/login`: 5 attempts per minute per IP
  - `/auth/refresh`: 10 per minute per user
  - `/auth/reset-password`: 3 per hour per email
- Never log passwords, tokens, or patient health data — use `@JsonIgnore` and log masking.
- All CORS allowed origins must be explicit whitelist — never `*` in production.

### Database & JPA
- **Never use `ddl-auto: create` or `ddl-auto: update` in any environment** — Flyway owns all schema changes.
- All schema changes go in `src/main/resources/db/migration/V{n}__{description}.sql`.
- Use `@Version` on any entity subject to concurrent updates (Slot, Appointment).
- Use soft delete pattern with `@SQLDelete` and `@Where`:
```java
@SQLDelete(sql = "UPDATE {table} SET deleted = true WHERE id = ?")
@Where(clause = "deleted = false")
```
- Never use `FetchType.EAGER` — always `LAZY` with explicit joins when needed.
- Always use `external_id` (UUID) in API DTOs, never expose `id` (Long).
- Use `TIMESTAMPTZ` for all date columns, store in UTC, convert to user timezone in frontend.

### Appointment & Slot Booking
- Slot booking must use optimistic locking (`@Version`) to prevent double-booking.
- `/join-call` endpoint must validate:
  1. Appointment belongs to authenticated user
  2. Appointment status is `CONFIRMED`
  3. Current time is within ±15 minutes of appointment time
  4. Generate Agora token with `appointmentId` as channel name
- Appointment must track call state machine:
  `PENDING → CONFIRMED → CALL_INITIATED → CALL_IN_PROGRESS → CALL_ENDED → COMPLETED`
- Store `call_start_time` and `call_end_time` on every appointment.

### Prescription Rules
- Prescriptions are **immutable once issued** — no UPDATE allowed, only new version.
- Every prescription PDF must include doctor's NMC registration number.
- Prescription file URLs must be signed/expiring URLs (S3/Supabase Storage) — never public permanent URLs.
- Soft delete only — never hard delete prescriptions (legal requirement).

### Audit Logging
- Use Spring AOP to log every: prescription access, appointment status change, user role change.
- Audit log must capture: `userId`, `action`, `resourceType`, `resourceId`, `timestamp`, `ipAddress`.
- Audit logs are append-only — no update, no delete ever.

### Service Layer Pattern
```java
// ✅ Correct
@Service
@Transactional
public class AppointmentService {
    public AppointmentResponse bookAppointment(BookingRequest request, Long patientId) {
        Slot slot = slotRepository.findByIdWithLock(request.getSlotId())
            .orElseThrow(() -> new SlotNotFoundException(request.getSlotId()));
        // business logic here
    }
}

// ❌ Never put business logic in controller
@PostMapping("/appointments")
public ResponseEntity<?> book(@RequestBody BookingRequest req) {
    slot.setStatus(BOOKED); // NO
}
```

